<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="56" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="57.[813,1456,370,606]" pageId="57" pageNumber="56">
DISTRIBUTION, ECOLOGY AND CONSERVATION STATUS. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cavaco &amp; Keraudren" authorityYear="1956" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Xylopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="57" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dielsii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="56">Xylopia dielsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the coast of a small area of northeastern 
<collectingCountry name="Madagascar" pageId="57" pageNumber="56">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[884,951,423,447]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="82.[132,143,1799,1817]" captionTargetBox="[134,1453,214,1759]" captionTargetId="figure@82.[458,797,717,1245]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIG. 28. — Distributions of Xylopia ambanjensis Cavaco &amp; Keraudren, X. anomala, sp. nov., X. australis, sp.nov., X.beananensis Cavaco &amp; Keraudren, X. bemarivensis Diels,X.buxifolia Baill., X.capuronii Cavaco &amp; Keraudren,X. carinata, sp. nov., X. danguyella Ghesq. ex Cavaco &amp; Keraudren, X. dielsii Cavaco &amp; Keraudren, X. fananehanensis Cavaco &amp; Keraudren, and X. flexuosa Diels on Madagascar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3877272" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3877272/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="56">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). It seems to be yet another microendemic species of the littoral and sublittoral humid forest on sand that occurs along the eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[928,1044,476,500]" name="Madagascar" pageId="57" pageNumber="56">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
coast. Specimens with flowers have been collected in November and December, and with fruits in February. Known from only three localities, and with an EOO and AOO of 
<quantity box="[813,889,555,579]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.61" pageId="57" pageNumber="56" unit="km" value="461.0">461 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[889,898,555,572]" fontSize="7" pageId="57" pageNumber="56">2</superScript>
and 
<quantity box="[946,1010,555,580]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="57" pageNumber="56" unit="km" value="12.0">12 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1010,1019,555,572]" fontSize="7" pageId="57" pageNumber="56">2</superScript>
, respectively, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cavaco &amp; Keraudren" authorityYear="1956" box="[1155,1238,555,579]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Xylopia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="57" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dielsii">
<emphasis box="[1155,1238,555,579]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="56">X. dielsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given a preliminary conservation assessment of Endangered (
<tableCitation box="[1211,1283,582,606]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="18.[214,225,221,239]" captionText="TABLE 2. — Preliminary and published conservation assessments for Madagascar and Mascarene Xylopia species.Abbreviations:CR, Critically Endangered; D, based on IUCN Criterion D; DD, Data Deficient; EN, Endangered; VU, Vulnerable. Sources: 1, Page 1998a; 2, Lantoarisoa 2015; 3, Callmander et al. 2009; 4, Page 1998b; 5, Page 1998c. *, See Discussion under X. flexuosa Diels." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/9DAB663AFFEFFFFEFF0A52C5370AFEBF" pageId="57" pageNumber="56" tableUuid="9DAB663AFFEFFFFEFF0A52C5370AFEBF">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
